OL,3,CMan who caused head-on crash after
OL,4,Cdriving on wrong side of the road is
OL,5,Cjailed
OL,7,FThe victim has been unable to walk
OL,8,Funaided since the collision.
OL,10,FPolice say the man continues to
OL,11,Fstruggle with 'simple everyday tasks,
OL,12,Fwhich has impacted heavily on both his
OL,13,Fand his family's lives'.
OL,15,FSergeant Vicki Rees from the Roads
OL,16,FPolicing Unit said: "The victim's life
OL,17,Fhas been changed immeasurably as a
OL,18,Fresult of this collision.
